This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Andrea Jones in court.  Prosecuting attorney Michael J. Odden in court for the State of Wisconsin. Hearing held via zoom. OFF THE RECORD.

Defendant has warrant issued and was instructed to be booked and clear warrant in out of custody intake court.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE BENCH  WARRANT.

Defendant Andrea Jones not in court.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear for a Book and Release by 8/3/2022, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO COMMISSIONER. No action taken on bail.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 8/3/2022. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR, A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Pawn America.
Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Andrea Jones in court.  Grant Ian Huebner appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 01. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 01.
  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 24, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 8/1/22 @ 2p
